    "comments": [
      "Taper: \"I've raided my cassette archive again and found another complete and previously unshared Friday Rock Show. This time we go back to the 10th July 1992. The session is from Soundgarden (who give us their interpretation of some classic songs) and, in addition to another excellent Rock War, there are some prime cuts from Metallica, L7, Mr Big, Queensryche and Gary Moore. Speed corrected and in high quality FM stereo it is again time for TV to play that rock'n'roll....Enjoy!\"",
      "The first heat of a new Rock War (Round 7, Heat 1): MZR come from County Durham; Rich Rags, Hull; and Crisis, Dunbartonshire."
    ]
  },
